Ministerial advisory committee chairperson, Professor Salim Abdool Karim full presentation. JOHANNESBURG - Professor Salim Abdool Karim says South Africa's low infection numbers compared with countries like the UK cannot be attributed to low testing. Karim is chairperson of the COVID-19 Ministerial Advisory Committee. He says as much as South Africa isn't doing enough testing, more tests are being done now than when COVID-19 first broke out in the country. COVID-19: Professor Karim's full presentation Karim was speaking a public meeting held by Health Minister, Dr Zweli Mkhize on Monday. He outlined some measures the country needs to take to contain COVID-19.